The article is a press release from the White House, dated April 5, 2011. The Secretary of Press made statements regarding the approval of H.R. 4. The Secretary stated that President Obama is open to working with both Republicans and Democrats to improve healthcare reform. The Congress has corrected an error that imposed unnecessary financial burdens on small businesses by removing the requirement to report 1099 forms. The Secretary emphasized the importance of small businesses in the economy and expressed the government's willingness to work with anyone who has ideas to make healthcare better and more affordable for all Americans.